<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11497&amp;p=133455#p133455"><![CDATA[
And on monitors that display 240p natively, such as CRT SDTVs, flashing large areas of the background could be grounds for a seizure trigger lawsuit. Remember the brouhaha about the <em>Pokémon</em> episode <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denn%C5%8D_Senshi_Porygon" class="postlink">&quot;Cyber Soldier Porygon&quot;</a> where Pikachu shorted out a missile, causing most of the screen to turn into a strobe light? It sent almost 700 real people to hospitals across Japan.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Sep 03, 2014 7:44 am</p><hr />
